# Documentation Rules — {Agent Name}

This agent generates docs that conform to the platform-wide rules. The rules are enforced by MCP `doc_lint` (code); this file describes them in {agent-slug}'s context.

## Required for every generated document

1. **YAML frontmatter** with keys: `feature-id`, `agent`, `phase`, `schema-version`, `gates-passed`
2. **Auto-generated TOC** at the top of every multi-section doc
3. **AI Summary** section at the top of the doc explaining why the AI created it
4. **Numbered sections** for cross-reference: `FR-NN` for requirements, `TS-NN` for technical specs, `TC-NN` for test cases
5. **Mermaid only** for diagrams — no PNG, no draw.io, no proprietary formats
6. **Traceability matrix** at the bottom of spec, plan, and TDD docs
7. **No inline ALM IDs** — section IDs only; ALM mapping lives in `work-items.yaml`

## Agent-specific rendering rules

If this agent has rules unique to its platform (e.g., a particular section sequence, mandatory marker conventions, multi-file pack assembly), document them here.

## Quality self-check appendix

Per ADR-0001, FDD, TDD, blueprint, and test-plan docs include a "Quality self-check" appendix at the bottom showing the findings from the inline check against `templates/checklists/{doc}-review.checklist.md`. `doc_lint` enforces the appendix's presence and fails the write on BLOCKER findings.

## Feature-id tagging (domain-scoped agents only)

If this agent has `docScope.{fdd|tdd|blueprint} = domain` in `agents.yaml`, every section block in the domain doc carries an `<!-- feature-id: {feature-slug} -->` HTML comment at the top, and every table row has a `feature-id` column. See `design/adr/0006-doc-scope-domain-vs-feature.md`.
